-- Irish 10-Year Government Bond Yield Premium Over Bunds Increases to Record
-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 2010-11-01T09:30:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/irish-10-year-bond-yield-premium-over-bunds-widens-to-a-record-455-points.html
The extra yield investors demand to
hold 10-year Irish government bonds instead of benchmark German
bunds widened to a record.  The difference in yield, or  spread , reached 455 basis
points as of 9:27 a.m. in London, the most since Bloomberg began
collecting the data in 1991.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Dobson in London at 
 pdobson2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
